The paper deals with game theory and equilibrium concepts, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) category. The use of preference relations and the study of strategies also indicate a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on graph structures and the use of algorithms to find equilibria suggest a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.SI).
